[Arena / Stage Modifier]
author=BigBossman
description=Using Value "14" with the "Elimination Chamber Modifier" code in the match rules section make the entire chamber appear, but you won't be able to climb around on it like normal.
Values - 
00 - Smackdown
01 - Raw
02 - ECW
03 - Tribute To The Troops
04 - Summerslam
05 - Breaking Point
06 - Hell In A Cell
07 - Survivor Series
08 - TLC
09 - Royal Rumble
0A - Elimination Chamber
0B - Wrestlemania
0C - Backlash
0D - Judgement Day
0E - Night of Champions
0F - The Bash
10 - Extreme Rules
11 - Superstars
12 - Bragging Rights
13 - Druid Arena
14 - Elimination Chamber W/ Invisible Elimination Chamber
15 - FROZE
16 - Royal Rumble
17 - Create-A-Move Set Arena (Arena is Empty)
18 - Empty, Pitch Blck Arena (except for the Ring)
19 - Old Smackdown with Fist Arena (Arena is Empty)
1A - Froze
patch=1,EE,006BC750,extended,00000000

[Match Rules Modifiers\Captain Falls / Elimination Modifier]
author=BigBossman
description=In WWE Smackdown: Shut Your Mouth & Here Comes the Pain, there was a match mode called Captain Falls. This mode wasn't in any of the other Smackdown Vs. Raw games that followed HCTP. The way it works is, if the tag team captain gets eliminated, the entire team loses. However, any of the other team member getting eliminated won't cost them the match. This works for any variation of Tag Team, 6-Man Tag Team, or even Handicapped matches. In addition, this also seems to act as a an elimination modifier as well. When playing a Triple Threat, Fatal 4-Way, or Armageddon Hell In A Cell Match, you'll have to eliminate everyone in the match in order to be declared the winner.
Values - 
00 - Captain Falls / Elimination is Off
01 - Captain Falls / Elimination is On
patch=1,EE,006BC72E,extended,00000000

[Match Rules Modifiers\Championship Scramble Modifier]
author=BigBossman
description=This won't actually cause additional competitors to run to the ring during a match, but the commentators will talk about the about the match being a Championship Scramble match when activated. If its turned off, when selecting a Championship Scramble match, the first two competitors in the ring will battle it out & no one else will come to the ring. Once time runs out, whoever got a win, will win that title.
Values - 
00 - Championship Scramble is Off
01 - Championship Scramble is On
patch=1,EE,006BC74C,extended,00000000

[Match Rules Modifiers\Count Out Modifier]
author=BigBossman
description=Modifies the number of seconds players are allowed to stay outside the ring before being counted out.
patch=1,EE,006BC715,extended,00000000

[Match Rules Modifiers\Disqualifications Modifier]
author=BigBossman
description=Values – 
00 – Disqualifications are Always Off
01 – Disqualifications are Always On
patch=1,EE,006BC72B,extended,00000000

[Match Rules Modifiers\Elimination Chamber Modifier]
author=BigBossman
description=Every match will have the Elimination Chamber, but its not perfect. While you can walk around the outer parts of it & can't access the weapons under the ring, you can still pass through the chamber & move near the commentator booth or move onto the ramp & stage area. Might need to be paired with an arena modifier code.
Values - 
00 - Elimination Chamber Match Always Off
01 - Elimination Chamber Match Always On 
patch=1,EE,006BC739,extended,00000000

[Match Rules Modifiers\Elimination Tag Match Modifier]
author=BigBossman
description=When enabled, all members of a tag team must be eliminated in order to win. 
Values - 
00 - Elimination Tag Match Always Off
01 - Elimination Tag Match Always On 
patch=1,EE,006BC72D,extended,00000000

